In a message dated 2/17/2002 1:57:16 PM Pacific Standard Time, 
duckyman(-at-)swbell.net writes:
> The the new drum seal bore is 1 or 2mm. larger than the old VW original 
> drums.
>    Has anyone run into this problem and, if so, how did you correct it?

Hi Duck,
Sounds like you need to contact a local machine shop and have them make two 
ringlike shims to be pressed in there to take up the extra room.

>    Also, does anyone make a reproduction of the tiny clip on the rear brakes 
> that hold the crossbar to the lower spring?

Get out a piece of banding strap, a pair of tin snips, a hammer and chisel.  
Then make your own!  Then drill,tap, and screw these into place.
Eric&Barb

